# Feature: Comprehensive Evaluation of Component-wise Contention
# Logic: All-to-all pair comparison (Ohta's Asymmetry Matrix)
# After stripping, ≥ 5 components are necessary.
# The ratio is the last step to the goal.
# Take the ratio using the Invariant Anchor as the basis. 
# The UTR absolute variation will be reconstructed as a ratio of basis data using the Invariant Anchor.
